<!-- @generated by scripts/generate-skill.ts — DO NOT EDIT.
     Regenerate via \`pnpm skill:gen\`; drift gated by \`pnpm skill:check\`. -->

This skill teaches an agent to operate \`difyctl\`, the Dify command-line interface. Every command supports \`-o json\` for stable, machine-readable output — always pass it.

Generated against difyctl v9.9.9-test. Run \`difyctl version\` to confirm your
binary matches; if it differs, refetch or regenerate this skill.

## Discovering the full command surface

This file does not freeze the full command set. Fetch it, machine-readable, in
one call:

    difyctl help -o json

That returns every command (description, args, flags, examples, agentGuide,
effect) plus the contract below.

## Contract

OUTPUT FORMATS
  json, yaml, name, wide, text

EXIT CODES
  0  success
  1  generic error
  2  usage error (bad flag / missing arg), or a workflow paused for human input
  4  auth error (not logged in / token expired)
  6  version / compatibility error

ERRORS
  On failure the error goes to stderr. Under -o json/yaml it is a structured envelope; otherwise a human line.
    { "error": { "code": string, "message": string, "hint"?: string, "http_status"?: number, "request"?: string } }

HUMAN-IN-THE-LOOP
  When a workflow pauses for human input, \`run app\` exits 2 and writes a JSON object to stdout with status "paused", form_token, workflow_run_id and resolved_default_values.
  Resume: difyctl resume app <app_id> <form_token> --workflow-run-id <id> [--inputs '{"key":"value"}']

## Safety

difyctl commands are classified by what they do to remote state. Read-only commands are safe to call freely and are not listed here. Confirm intent before any command below, and treat \`destructive\` commands as irreversible.

write — side effects, mostly recoverable:
  auth login           Sign in to Dify via OAuth device flow
  auth logout          Log out of the active Dify host
  config set           Set a config key (validates value)
  config unset         Reset a config key to its zero value
  create member        Invite a member to the active (or specified) workspace by email
  resume app           Resume a paused workflow app after submitting a human input form
  run app              Run an app and print the response
  set member           Change a member's role in the active (or specified) workspace
  use workspace        Switch the active workspace on the server and refresh hosts.yml

destructive — irreversible / data loss:
  auth devices revoke  Revoke one or all session devices
  delete member        Remove a member from the active (or specified) workspace

## Core workflow

1. difyctl auth login  — Sign in to Dify via OAuth device flow
     $ difyctl auth login

2. difyctl get app  — List apps or describe one app's basic info
     $ difyctl get app

3. difyctl describe app  — Describe a single app (kubectl-describe-style)
     $ difyctl describe app app-1

4. difyctl run app  — Run an app and print the response
     $ difyctl run app app-1 "hello"

5. difyctl resume app  — Resume a paused workflow app after submitting a human input form
     $ difyctl resume app app-1 ft-abc --workflow-run-id wf-run-1 --action submit --inputs '{"name":"Alice"}'

If \`difyctl run app\` exits 2 the workflow paused for human input (see
HUMAN-IN-THE-LOOP above); resume it with \`difyctl resume app\`.

